{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μῆνις</b>, <br /> <i>Doric dialect</i> and <i>Aeolic dialect</i> <b>μᾶν-</b>, ἡ, <i>genitive</i> μήνιος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 390e, later μήνιδος 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Fragmenta” 80, 4th c.AD: Themistius Sophista “Orationes” 22.265d, 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Orationes” 2.50b, “Anthologia Graeca” 9.168 (6th c.AD: Palladas Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>wrath</b>; from [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] downwards frequently of the <b>wrath</b> of the gods, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.34, +others, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 701 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 880e, 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 585 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μῆνιν ἔχειν ἀπὸ θεοῦ Vett.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Val. 184.3; μ. χθονίων 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.159 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also of the dead worshipped as heroes, τοῖσι μ. κατέσκηψε Ταλθυβίου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.134, compare 137; μ. τῶν τετελευτηκότων 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Hp.Ma.” 282a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of injured parents, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 155 (Lyric poetry), “Ch.” 294 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of suppliants, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Eu.” 234, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 762 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: but also, generally, of the <b>wrath</b> of Achilles, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.1, +others, compare 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 10.7\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of the <b>revengeful temper</b> of a people, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 21, 5th c.BC: